  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance to Flood Affected Communities in North-West Districts of Bangladesh 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As Consortium lead CA is going to implement Response project in three unions of Fulchari,Gaibandah with START fund. Christian Aid will target extremely marginalised and poor communities who are severely affected by flood and have lost their food stocks, standing crops, houses, and other household, belongings as well as those households who lost their WASH facilities (damage of latrine, water point etc.)   Special emphasis would be given to women, children, adolescent girls, elderly people, people from excluded community and minority group. Each 1166 HHs will receive Emergency shelter materials, hygiene kits and cash BDT 4000, Total value of the package is BDT 6000.  ACF &amp; Muslim Aid Is the member of the consortium and GUK is the implementing partner of CA. Through this project Total 3457 HHs will be supported by consortium partner.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Total 1166HH will receive the sheltrNFI &amp; WASH support that will enhance their accessibility to safe drinking water annd safe shelter
b.Health risk reduced among the benefited families due to WASH support(NFI,Hygiene kits Soap, Alum &amp; ORS);
- Most vulnerable such as PWD,children, elderly, women &amp; extremely poor are protected  in these difficult times.
-Health Hygiene knowledge has been increased among the people</narrative>
  </description>
